'If they can hear, their auditory system must be a survivor of
life forms on the ancient supercontinent Gondwana.'

In order to test if the frogs really do use sound to communicate, the scientists set up loudspeakers in their natural habitat and broadcast pre-recorded frog songs.

This caused males present in the rainforest to answer, proving that they were able to hear the sound from the loudspeakers.

